Ready in less than 25 minutes, this Speedy Tomato Cajun Chicken Breast has it all. Punchy and smoky with a spicy kick, Cajun spice mix contains ingredients such as chilli powder, ground cumin, oregano and thyme.

> This recipe serves 2.

== Potatoes ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{}.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%mins}.

== Cajun Chicken ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken has browned, add the garlic and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer.

Cook until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Finishing ==

Once the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked, stir through the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted, ~{1-2%mins}.

== Mashed Potato ==

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, spoon the creamy tomato Cajun chicken into your #bowls{}.

Serve the mash alongside. Enjoy!